<p><br />The Department of History encourages students to:</p>
<ol>
<li>Have a solid understanding of, and interest in, U.S. and world history, and a sense of the complexities of human experience</li>
<li>Read and write well</li>
<li>Communicate publicly and participate in small teams</li>
<li>Have some knowledge of doing research in a university library</li>
<li>Discuss history on a general political, social, and moral level.</li>
</ol>
<p>In addition, History Education majors should develop a size-able repertoire of lessons, pedagogies, and approaches to history, which are appropriate for teaching at the secondary level.</p>
